      <h1 class='title'>Children in Poverty</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 cc1728-9WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_1728ws' title='Col. 1728WS &mdash; HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1728WS' name='column_1728ws' href='#column_1728ws' rel='bookmark'>1728WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_461'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-shaun-woodward' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_461' title='Link to this speech by Mr Shaun Woodward' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-shaun-woodward" title="Mr Shaun Woodward">Mr. Woodward</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions (1) what estimate the Government have
          <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_1729ws' title='Col. 1729WS &mdash; HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1729WS' name='column_1729ws' href='#column_1729ws' rel='bookmark'>1729WS</a>
          made of <span class="italic">(a)</span> how many and <span class="italic">(b)</span> what percentage of children lived in poverty in (i) St. Helens and (ii) the UK, broken down by region, in each year since 1997; [186825]</p><p>(2) what estimate the Government have made of <span class="italic">(a)</span> how many and <span class="italic">(b)</span> what percentage of children lived in low-income households in (i) St. Helens and (ii) the UK, broken down by region, in each year since 1997; [186824]</p><p>(3) what the Government's performance has been against each of its child poverty reduction targets in <span class="italic">(a)</span> St. Helens and <span class="italic">(b)</span> the UK, broken down by region, since 1997. [186806]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_462'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-chris-pond' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_462' title='Link to this speech by Mr Chris Pond' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-chris-pond" title="Mr Chris Pond">Mr. Pond</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">Poverty and social exclusion are complex and multi-dimensional issues, affecting many aspects of peoples' lives&#x2014;including their living standards, health, housing, the quality of their environment&#x2014;and not just low income. The sixth annual "Opportunity For All" report (Cm 6329) sets out the Governments strategy for tackling poverty and social exclusion and presents information on the indicators used to measure progress against this strategy.</p><p>Specific information regarding low income for Great Britain and the United Kingdom is available in "Households Below Average Income 1994&#x2013;95 to 2002&#x2014;03". Data are not available below regional level.</p><p>"Measuring Child Poverty", published in December 2003, outlines the Government's measure of UK child poverty for the long term. This new measure will begin from 2004&#x2013;05.</p><p>All publications listed are available in the Library.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
